{
  "stem": "19690.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Soon, the rumors were that the-- that everybody was going to be deported back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that point, the committee came to the parents of the younger children and said that they can take everyone under 18 out of the camp and get them into homes, children's homes.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I absolutely refused to do anything of the sort.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wanted to go with my mother and father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By this time, my parents had been permitted to sleep in the same area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The mothers-- the women and men started moving in together and I was there, too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the discussion was frequent and constant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Mrs.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Solomon, who had been a good friend, who was the director of OSE in southern France that I had known for many years, came to see us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had been in a summer camp called Chateau [NON-ENGLISH] in the summer of 1941 for a month and liked it very much.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she said to me, I don't want you to go with your parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I want you to stay with us and I will take you back to [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This was a promise that she made to me and which she kept.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So a decision was made that my things would be separated from everybody else's and I would leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My parents were very sad-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --and yet they were upbeat towards me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But you can feel it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "On the 10th of August, buses rolled into the camp and it was time for us to leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We assembled by the buses and there was a guard at each bus.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I still see him sitting there-- standing.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
